      <section eId="sec_3409">
        <num>3409</num>
        <heading>State and county not liable on corporation bonds</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_3409__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The\nstate shall not be liable on the bonds or notes of the corporation and\nsuch bonds or notes shall not be a debt of the state, and such bonds and\nnotes shall contain on the face thereof a statement to such effect.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_3409__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as may be authorized by the county pursuant to section\nseven of article seventeen of the state constitution and section\nthirty-four hundred seven of this title, the county shall not be liable\non the bonds or notes of the corporation and such bonds or notes shall\nnot be a debt of the county, and such bonds and notes shall contain on\nthe face thereof a statement to such effect or a statement describing\nthe county liability thereon, if any.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
